| accessdate=2009-10-02
}}</ref>

===21st Century Cancer Access to Life-Saving Early detection, Research and Treatment (ALERT) Act===

The [[United States Senate|US Senate]] on 26 March 2009 issued a new bill (S. 717), the [[21st Century Cancer Access to Life-Saving Early detection, Research and Treatment (ALERT) Act]]<ref>{{cite web
| title=S.717: 21st Century Cancer ALERT (Access to Life-Saving Early detection, Research and Treatment) Act
| url=http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=s111-717
| publisher=GovTrack.us, 111th Congress (2009–2010)
| date=2009-03-26
| author=Senators [[Ted Kennedy|Edward Kennedy]] and [[Kay Bailey Hutchison]]
| accessdate=2009-03-30
}}</ref>
intended to "overhaul the 1971 National Cancer Act."<ref name=KenHutchBillNews />
The bill aims to improve patient access to [[Cancer#Prevention|prevention]] and early detection by:
# providing funding for research in early detection,
# supplying grants for screening and referrals for treatment, and
# increasing access to clinical trials and information.

