In a cancer research funding announcement made by president Obama in September 2009, TCGA project is slated to receive $175 million in funding to collect comprehensive gene sequence data on 20,000 tissue samples from people with more than 20 different types of cancer, in order to help researchers understand the genetic changes underlying cancer. New, targeted therapeutic approaches are expected to arise from the insights resulting from such studies.<ref name=obamaSep09 />

====Cancer Genome Project====
The [[Cancer Genome Project]] at the [[Sanger Institute|Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute]] aims to identify [[genetic variation|sequence variant]]s/[[mutation]]s critical in the development of human [[cancer]]s. The Cancer Genome Project combines knowledge of the [[human genome]] sequence with [[high-throughput screening|high throughput mutation detection]] techniques.<ref>{{cite web
| url=http://www.sanger.ac.uk/genetics/CGP/
| title=The Cancer Genome Project website
| work=Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute
| accessdate=2009-02-14
}}</ref>

